--Configuration

include tp_widgets in your rc.lua with 
	require("path/to/tp_widgets")

Then you can create power widgets with
	tp_widgets.create_power_widget([optional: use_short_format,pdate_frequency])
and battery widgets with
	tp_widgets.create_battery_widget([optional: use_short_format, update_frequency])

With the boolean option use_short_format you can chose between the default ("charging", "discharging", "ac power")
and the short ("C", "D", "AC") format.

You can handle them as standard awesome-textbox-widgets.
